definition.value: A blasticidin that is an antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces griseochromogene.
A glycosylfucose consisting of an alpha-D-galactopyranose residue and an alpha-L-fucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A disaccharide phosphate consisting of a 6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannopyranose residue and an alpha-D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A choline that is the parent compound of the cholines class, consisting of ethanolamine having three methyl substituents attached to the amino function.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl tetrasaccharide units are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine trisaccharide.
A methyl D-glucopyranuronate in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
Actylcholine is an ester of acetic acid and choline, which acts as a neurotransmitter.
An L-idofuranose that has alpha configuration at the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group.
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is propanoic acid with an amino group at position 2 and a sulfanyl group at position 3.
